+# Why CVE-2026-32741 Does Not Affect `libheif` 1.11.0 on Debian Bullseye
+
+## CVE-2026-32741 – Heap Buffer Overflow via Unbounded `memcpy` in Mask Image Decoding
+
+- **Component:** `MaskImageCodec::decode_mask_image()` function
+- **CWE:** CWE-787 (Out-of-bounds Write), CWE-120 (Buffer Copy without Checking Size of Input)
+- **Issue:** The full `iloc` extent data is copied into a fixed-size pixel buffer with `memcpy(dst, data.data(), data.size())`, where `data.size()` is attacker-controlled and the destination is sized from the declared image dimensions. With no upper-bound check, a crafted file whose extent exceeds the buffer overflows the heap.
+- **Fix Commit:** `123694271ac02f2de68a3ccdc5d483eb8a2ae593`
+- **Upstream Status:** Fixed in upstream `libheif` 1.22.0
+
+---
+
+## Why Debian Bullseye (`libheif` 1.11.0-1+deb11u2) Is NOT Affected
+
+The vulnerability lives in the `MaskImageCodec` mask-image (`mski` / `mskC`) subsystem, which was **added to `libheif` years after v1.11.0**. The entire feature — and therefore the vulnerable code path — does not exist in v1.11.0.
+
+### Root Cause Analysis
+
+The fix commit changes `libheif/image-items/mask_image.cc`:
+
+```cpp
+- if (((uint32_t)stride) == width) {
+-   memcpy(dst, data.data(), data.size());          // vulnerable: attacker-controlled length
++ if (stride == static_cast<size_t>(width)) {
++   memcpy(dst, data.data(), static_cast<size_t>(width) * height);   // fixed: bounded to pixel buffer
+````
+
+The single-`memcpy` branch is reached when the `mskC` property specifies `bits_per_pixel = 8` and the `ispe` property declares an even width >= 64 (so that `stride == width`).
+
+In v1.11.0, **none of this code exists**:
+
+* `MaskImageCodec` was first introduced upstream in commit `94f9a09e`, released in **v1.17.0**.
+* The specific vulnerable single-`memcpy` branch was introduced in commit `b6a77bff`, released in **v1.19.0**.
+* There is no `libheif/image-items/` directory, no `mask_image.cc`, and no `mski` / `mskC` box parsing of any kind in v1.11.0.
+
+### Version Comparison
+
+| Version                     | File                    | `MaskImageCodec` present? | Vulnerable `memcpy` branch? | Affected? |
+| --------------------------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------- | --------------------------- | --------- |
+| v1.11.0 (Bullseye)          | (none — feature absent) | NO                        | NO                          | NO        |
+| v1.17.0 – v1.18.x           | `mask_image.cc`         | YES                       | NO (branch not yet added)   | NO        |
+| v1.19.0 – v1.21.2 (pre-fix) | `mask_image.cc`         | YES                       | YES                         | YES       |
+| v1.22.0 (post-fix)          | `mask_image.cc`         | YES                       | bounded copy                | NO        |
+
+### Debian Bullseye Package Details
+
+| Field            | Value                |
+| ---------------- | -------------------- |
+| Package          | libheif              |
+| Version          | 1.11.0-1+deb11u2     |
+| Distribution     | Debian 11 (Bullseye) |
+| Upstream Version | 1.11.0               |
+| Status           | **NOT AFFECTED**     |
+
+---
+
+## Why the Fix Cannot Be Applied
+
+The upstream fix modifies `libheif/image-items/mask_image.cc`. On v1.11.0 this patch:
+
+* **Cannot apply** — the target file, the `MaskImageCodec` class, and the `decode_mask_image()` function do not exist.
+* **Is not needed** — there is no equivalent mask-image decoding path elsewhere in v1.11.0, so there is no vulnerable `memcpy` to bound.
+
+### Verification
+
+All three checks below return empty on the v1.11.0 source tree, confirming the vulnerable code is absent:
+
+```bash
+grep -rn "MaskImageCodec\|decode_mask_image" libheif/   # codec class / function
+grep -rn "mskC\|mski\|MaskImage" libheif/                # mask-image box parsing
+ls libheif/image-items/mask_image.cc                     # the file the patch modifies
+```
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+* CVE-2026-32741 affects the `MaskImageCodec` subsystem, introduced in v1.17.0 (vulnerable branch in v1.19.0)
+* That subsystem does not exist in v1.11.0 — no `mask_image.cc`, no `mski` / `mskC` handling, no vulnerable `memcpy`
+* Debian Bullseye's `libheif` 1.11.0-1+deb11u2 is **NOT AFFECTED**
+* No patch is required; the upstream fix cannot even be applied because the target code does not exist
+
+**Status: NOT_AFFECTED — No action needed.**
+
+---
+
